The concentrated supernatant (100 μL), with ACE2 activity of 43.3 nM/mL/min and specific activity of 7.41 nM/mg was applied to an ion-exchange column equilibrated with 25 mM Tris–HCl buffer, pH 8,0, containing 10 μM ZnCl2. ACE2 enzymatic activity was eluted as one peak with specific activity of 40.3 nM/mg and was purified 5.4 fold (Fig. 1
and Table 1
).
